I"Á+<p>They say there are two hard problems in computer science: Caching, Naming things, and off by one errors.</p>

<p>No? Ok.</p>

<p>Let‚Äôs talk about naming things. I don‚Äôt think it has to be that hard.  I have a few guidelines to keep in mind that go beyond the usual suspects. Let‚Äôs run through them real quick.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Most important words first</li>
  <li>Consider the scoping</li>
</ol>

<!--
