<h2 id="most-important-words-first">Most important words first.</h2>
<p>This is a specific use case of my more general principle ‚Äúmost important thing first‚Äù.</p>

<p>So frequently I will see developers write variables as they may speak them, and yes I do think that is good sometimes, the problem though is English grammar isn‚Äôt the best.  I like Spanish grammar better.  In case you don‚Äôt know in Spanish you generally place the noun before the adjective, and verbs before adverbs.  Everyone agrees this makes sense.  The reason it makes sense is because it puts the most important words first.</p>

<p>I would say consider this when choosing variable names.  One of the reasons why I like this is because it can make your code more scannable.  Let‚Äôs take a look at an example.  Many moons ago, working on an application, we needed some colors.  Thus _colors.scss was born.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-css" data-lang="css"><span class="nd">:root</span> <span class="p">{</span>
  <span class="py">--gray-white-color</span> <span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#FFFFFF</span>
  <span class="n">--gray-medium-color</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#AAAAAA</span>
  <span class="n">--gray-black-color</span> <span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#000000</span>
  <span class="n">--blue-light-color</span> <span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#48CAE4</span>
  <span class="n">--blue-medium-color</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#00B4D8</span>
  <span class="n">--blue-dark-color</span>  <span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#023E8A</span>
<span class="p">}</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>Lets take a look at an alternative, more common, naming scheme.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-css" data-lang="css"><span class="nd">:root</span> <span class="p">{</span>
  <span class="py">--white-color</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#FFFFFF</span>
  <span class="n">--medium-gray-color</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#AAAAAA</span>
  <span class="n">--black-gray-color</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#000000</span>
  <span class="n">--light-blue-color</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#48CAE4</span>
  <span class="n">--medium-blue-color</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#00B4D8</span>
  <span class="n">--dark-blue-color</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#023E8A</span>
<span class="p">}</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>Now maybe you don‚Äôt agree with suffixing the type just yet.  We will talk about that later, but it doesn‚Äôt help.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-css" data-lang="css"><span class="nd">:root</span> <span class="p">{</span>
  <span class="py">--white</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#FFFFFF</span>
  <span class="n">--medium-gray</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#AAAAAA</span>
  <span class="n">--black-gray</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#000000</span>
  <span class="n">--light-blue</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#48CAE4</span>
  <span class="n">--medium-blue</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#00B4D8</span>
  <span class="n">--dark-blue</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">#023E8A</span>
<span class="p">}</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>One of these is clearly easier on the eyes.  It should be clear that when you put the most important word first, the characters automatically align themselves, making it easier for your eyes to scan a block of text.  Next time try pushing your nouns to the front of your variables, and your verbs to the front of your functions.  Then suffix with your adjectives and your adverbs.</p>

